<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>They prioritize storage over visibility.</strong> If seeds are hidden, they are less likely to be used effectively.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They overcomplicate organization.</strong> Complex systems are harder to maintain.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They do not update their system.</strong> Organization only works if it reflects current seed inventory.
  </p>
</section>

